{"metadata":{"title":"What’s new in Wallet and Apple Pay","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC20"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10662-whats-new-in-wallet-and-apple-pay"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Apple Pay makes it simple to pay for goods and services in your app and on your website. Discover how you can integrate API updates like context-specific button types, contact data formatting, and cross-platform support to make the service more effective for you and people using it. And, if you’re building app clips, adopting Apple Pay can help you unlock new commerce experiences.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10662-Whats-new-in-Wallet-and-Apple-Pay","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/passkit\/pkpaymentpass"},{"text":" has been replaced by a new class ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/passkit\/PKSecureElementPass"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKSecureElementPass"},{"type":"text","text":" has the same properties as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKPaymentPass"},{"type":"text","text":", so it’s encouraged to use this one."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/passkit\/PKPaymentButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" didn’t change much, however it has new ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/passkit\/pkpaymentbuttontype","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for renting, top up, etc..","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now the payment button can derive its light\/dark style theme from the system by supplying an automatic style to the button:","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["var automaticButton = PKPaymentButton(paymentButtonType: .plain, paymentButtonStyle: .automatic)"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We can also request specifically for light or dark mode in the same way","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now Catalyst and native macOS apps supports paying with Apple Pay in the same way it’s implemented on web pages"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Also, instead of asking the WebKit for a URL for Apple Pay and validate that URL against known Apple hostnames, there is a static URL you we always send our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"POST"},{"type":"text","text":" request to directly: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apple-pay-gateway.apple.com"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Contacts-formatting-improvements","text":"Contacts formatting improvements"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"in iOS 14, when contact data is coming from Apple Pay, qw will see more consistent data and less variation","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Also, users are now prompted to correct issues in their contact information earlier, so they get to fix it sooner in the process.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Written-By","text":"Written By"},{"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ATahhan"}],"type":"paragraph"}